WEBVTT

00:01.320 --> 00:03.320
As usual your honor. Mr. Swindel

00:03.320 --> 00:06.030
Is misrepresenting
the chain of events.

00:06.220 --> 00:08.250
When the officers entered
the premises...

00:08.250 --> 00:11.020
- they kicked in my client's
door without a warrant.

00:11.020 --> 00:12.220
- Is that true?

00:12.230 --> 00:13.990
- The officers heard
a toilet flushing.

00:13.990 --> 00:15.490
- Luis has a weak bladder.

00:15.500 --> 00:17.260
- The police didn't need
a warrant, your honor.

00:17.260 --> 00:19.830
There were clearly
exigent circumstances.

00:19.830 --> 00:21.230
- Yeah, that's right, for Luis.

00:21.230 --> 00:23.000
He downed a six-pack, judge.

00:23.000 --> 00:25.270
Under the fourth amendment,
that search was illegal.

00:25.270 --> 00:26.840
- It was clear to the officers

00:26.840 --> 00:29.210
that the defendant
was destroying his stash.

00:29.210 --> 00:30.340
- They have X-ray vision,
do they?

00:30.340 --> 00:32.210
- Move to exclude, your honor.

00:32.210 --> 00:34.550
- Done. Next.

00:34.550 --> 00:37.550
- Exigent circumstances.
Very nice.

00:37.550 --> 00:39.280
- Not nice enough.

00:39.290 --> 00:43.320
- Hey, you took a shot.
I respect that.

00:43.320 --> 00:46.220
- Ms. Valdez, approach
the bench, if you don't mind.

00:54.270 --> 00:55.400
8:00?

00:57.800 --> 00:59.570
Okay, enough already.

00:59.570 --> 01:01.310
I'll talk to her this week.

01:01.310 --> 01:04.010
- How many times
have I heard that?

01:04.010 --> 01:05.310
- This time I mean it.

01:05.310 --> 01:06.880
Where'd you park?
I'll walk you.

01:06.880 --> 01:09.250
- I'm fine.
I'm just around the corner.

01:09.250 --> 01:11.220
- Night, then.
- Goodnight.

01:14.820 --> 01:16.820
Drive safe.

01:38.310 --> 01:40.040
Ray?

01:42.980 --> 01:44.420
Ray?

01:44.420 --> 01:47.020
Help!
Oh, my god!

01:49.290 --> 01:51.120
- Oh, my...

01:51.120 --> 01:52.890
Help! Somebody help!

01:58.860 --> 02:01.430
- Yes, I need an ambulance.

02:01.430 --> 02:03.900
Uh, 2424 rush street.

02:03.900 --> 02:07.070
Stay with me, ray.

02:07.070 --> 02:08.410
Just keep breathing.

02:08.410 --> 02:10.270
Come on, ray, just stay with me.

02:15.380 --> 02:17.650
- Anna, I know it's hard,

02:17.650 --> 02:19.320
but if you can remember
anything else...

02:19.320 --> 02:21.950
Anything you heard,
anything you saw.

02:21.950 --> 02:23.390
Did you see
anyone else in the street?

02:23.390 --> 02:25.920
- I...

02:25.930 --> 02:28.430
I wasn't really looking.

02:28.430 --> 02:31.400
I got to my car,
I heard the shots,

02:31.400 --> 02:33.400
I saw a motorcycle...

02:34.970 --> 02:37.370
I heard four gunshots.
I definitely...

02:37.370 --> 02:41.310
Heard four gunshots.
- Yeah.

02:41.310 --> 02:43.310
Can I get you something?

02:43.310 --> 02:44.480
You sit tight.

02:44.480 --> 02:46.440
I'll be right back.
Sit tight.

02:48.380 --> 02:50.450
Officer.

02:56.350 --> 02:57.990
- How's she doing?

02:57.990 --> 03:00.090
- It's a tough thing to see.

03:00.090 --> 03:02.490
- Want me to take her home?
- No, I'll do it.

03:02.500 --> 03:04.160
- Pd found the shell casings.

03:04.160 --> 03:06.330
The shooter used a .32
close range.

03:06.330 --> 03:08.430
Feels like a hit.

03:08.430 --> 03:10.400
Kinzie sat on the bench
for 15 years.

03:10.400 --> 03:12.700
Probably put away
over 500 bad guys.

03:12.710 --> 03:15.110
- That's 500 motives.

03:15.110 --> 03:16.440
- I'll see if any of them
got out recently.

03:16.440 --> 03:19.340
Canvass the area.
Maybe somebody saw something.

03:28.220 --> 03:31.020
Hey, I'm gonna take you home.

03:31.020 --> 03:33.120
- How is he?
- Anna...

03:35.060 --> 03:37.090
I'm sorry.

03:43.070 --> 03:44.740
- Come on.
Come on.

03:59.650 --> 04:02.690
- The orange sticker
on the windscreen

04:02.690 --> 04:03.720
of the motorcycle.

04:03.720 --> 04:05.120
- As he drove toward me,

04:05.120 --> 04:07.190
I didn't see
the actual shooting.

04:07.190 --> 04:09.130
- And the guy on the bike...

04:09.130 --> 04:12.000
- Was wearing a full helmet
with a face shield.

04:13.060 --> 04:14.190
There's got to be
surveillance footage

04:14.190 --> 04:15.600
from the credit union
down the street.

04:15.600 --> 04:17.200
I'll call their security team
and we can...

04:17.200 --> 04:19.670
- The shooter had to have
passed it.

04:19.670 --> 04:21.470
- I said no, Anna.

04:21.470 --> 04:23.210
What were you doing
at Sheridan's?

04:28.050 --> 04:30.750
I was there having a drink,
just like everyone else.

04:30.750 --> 04:33.020
- With judge Kinzie?

04:33.020 --> 04:35.720
- I was there alone.
He came in.

04:35.720 --> 04:38.790
I lost the Diaz motion in front
of him that afternoon.

04:38.790 --> 04:43.030
He came over to say
no hard feelings.

04:43.030 --> 04:44.290
- That's it?

04:46.200 --> 04:48.730
Who was he with?
- I didn't notice.

04:48.730 --> 04:52.100
- And yet you left
the bar together.

04:55.070 --> 04:57.210
- I left the bar,
walked to my car,

04:57.210 --> 04:59.310
and heard the gunshots.

05:00.610 --> 05:02.710
Four of them.

05:06.620 --> 05:08.290
- Maybe you should take
a couple of days.

05:08.290 --> 05:11.390
- No, I'm okay.
I should get back to work.

05:13.260 --> 05:16.230
- Do they still teach about
the Chinese wall in law school?

05:17.630 --> 05:20.230
- No way, Peter.
No!

05:20.230 --> 05:22.270
You're not excluding me
from this investigation!

05:22.270 --> 05:27.100
The appearance of impropriety
alone could be a problem later.

05:27.110 --> 05:29.840
If I were you, I would go home
and rest for a couple of days.

05:29.840 --> 05:34.180
- Then there are plenty
of other cases on your desk.

05:42.550 --> 05:44.290
- I spoke with the mayor.

05:44.290 --> 05:48.690
"This rocks the foundation
of civilization," he says.

05:48.690 --> 05:50.760
- Five kids are killed over
the weekend, crickets.

05:50.760 --> 05:53.660
- Those kids weren't
at his daughter's wedding.

05:55.270 --> 05:59.170
Man. Man. Man.

05:59.170 --> 06:01.640
Every year ray and I
went ice fishing.

06:01.640 --> 06:05.180
Shabbona lake,
president's day weekend.

06:05.180 --> 06:09.210
Been doing it since
I was a rookie on the force,

06:09.220 --> 06:11.580
and he was fresh out
of law school.

06:11.580 --> 06:15.150
- I'm sorry, mark.

06:15.150 --> 06:18.120
- He could be her damn father.

06:18.120 --> 06:19.260
- Anna said they just happened

06:19.260 --> 06:20.720
to leave the bar
at the same time.

06:20.730 --> 06:23.730
- And you believe her?
- I do.

06:28.330 --> 06:29.670
Stone.

06:32.200 --> 06:33.670
Good.

06:33.670 --> 06:35.770
Okay.

06:35.770 --> 06:38.280
Cpd arrested a guy trying
to rob a liquor store.

06:38.280 --> 06:41.750
Ballistics says he was using
the same gun that killed Kinzie.

06:41.750 --> 06:43.350
He was on video
at a soup kitchen

06:43.350 --> 06:44.920
at the time of the shooting.

06:49.920 --> 06:52.220
- You know,
every new year's Eve,

06:52.220 --> 06:54.360
Raymond and I would
toast each other.

06:54.360 --> 06:57.160
And he would say, "this is it:".

06:57.160 --> 06:59.160
My last year on the bench."

06:59.170 --> 07:02.200
He could be a counsel
at a downtown firm.

07:02.200 --> 07:03.930
Have a big office,

07:03.940 --> 07:06.940
take clients to lunch or teach.

07:06.940 --> 07:09.410
That's what he really
wanted to do.

07:09.410 --> 07:12.940
We're very sorry, Mrs. Kinzie.

07:14.880 --> 07:18.920
- I apologize.
Um, can I get you something?

07:18.920 --> 07:20.350
People brought so much food.

07:20.350 --> 07:23.250
I think I have
six kinds of cake.

07:23.260 --> 07:25.760
Coffee.
- We're... we're fine,

07:25.760 --> 07:27.390
but if you could just tell us...

07:27.390 --> 07:29.460
- Where I was when ray died.

07:31.800 --> 07:34.460
I'm a suspect, aren't I?
- No, of course not.

07:34.470 --> 07:36.970
We were just wondering if your
husband happened to mention

07:36.970 --> 07:39.340
who he was meeting
at the bar that night.

07:39.340 --> 07:41.510
- No, I thought he was...

07:43.940 --> 07:47.380
After a long week, he liked
to have a quiet drink

07:47.380 --> 07:49.280
before he fought the traffic.

07:49.280 --> 07:50.810
- Did he mention any threats?

07:50.820 --> 07:52.720
Anyone that might
want to hurt him?

07:52.720 --> 07:54.350
- We decided a long time ago

07:54.350 --> 07:56.450
ray would never bring
his work home with him.

07:57.990 --> 08:00.290
- This your daughter?

08:00.290 --> 08:03.260
- Caitlin,
our foster daughter, yes.

08:03.260 --> 08:05.330
We're talking about
adopting her.

08:05.330 --> 08:06.960
- Hm. Can we talk to her?

08:06.970 --> 08:09.830
- She's actually not really
feeling very well.

08:09.840 --> 08:12.800
This whole thing has...
- I'm sure, but you never know.

08:12.810 --> 08:14.910
Caitlin might not even know
that she knows something.

08:14.910 --> 08:17.510
- She, um, took my car
and went shopping.

08:17.510 --> 08:20.510
- The Mercedes?
- Yes.

08:21.950 --> 08:24.510
- I saw a Mercedes parked
in your garage when we came in.

08:24.520 --> 08:27.320
She must've come home.
You didn't notice?

08:27.320 --> 08:29.520
- We're worried that someone
might try to hurt

08:29.520 --> 08:31.960
Caitlin or you, Mrs. Kinzie.
If the killer comes back...

08:31.960 --> 08:34.960
- I haven't seen her
since ray was...

08:34.960 --> 08:37.260
- where is she, Mrs. Kinzie?

08:41.000 --> 08:43.030
- She's run away before,
but she always comes back

08:43.039 --> 08:44.470
in a day or two.

08:49.010 --> 08:52.580
She and ray
were fighting a lot recently.

08:52.580 --> 08:54.340
- What about?

08:54.350 --> 08:56.450
- I don't know.
She's a teenager.

08:58.050 --> 09:00.350
- Can we see Caitlin's room?

09:01.350 --> 09:05.020
- No phone, no laptop...
There's lots of metal.

09:05.020 --> 09:08.030
- Hmm. Hell hath no fury
like a teenage girl.

09:08.030 --> 09:10.490
My daughter and I
went from best friends

09:10.500 --> 09:12.900
to mortal enemies overnight.

09:12.900 --> 09:15.330
Nothing can prepare you for
the wrath of your spawn.

09:18.840 --> 09:20.400
- Nope.

09:23.310 --> 09:24.940
She got a thing for birds.

09:26.410 --> 09:28.780
Lex Talionis?
- It's Latin.

09:28.780 --> 09:32.350
Means "eye for an eye."
- I'm impressed.

09:32.350 --> 09:35.490
- Head altar boy at St. John's.

09:35.490 --> 09:37.990
Free wine and incense.
What's not to like?

09:41.330 --> 09:43.630
- Looks like Caitlin was
a regular at cafe jumping bean.

09:43.630 --> 09:46.360
Maybe the barista knows
who she hangs out with.

09:49.870 --> 09:51.440
- May-December?

09:51.440 --> 09:52.640
It's my bread and butter.

09:52.640 --> 09:55.910
That's why they call this
the Viagra triangle.

09:55.910 --> 09:57.610
- All right.

09:57.610 --> 10:01.080
- Uh...
Yeah, sure.

10:01.080 --> 10:04.050
I think I seen her,
but the under-30s,

10:04.050 --> 10:06.120
they all start to look the same.

10:06.120 --> 10:08.420
What about this guy?

10:09.350 --> 10:12.120
- Oh, now him...
Him I recognize, yeah.

10:12.120 --> 10:13.560
Yeah, he was with the honey.

10:13.560 --> 10:16.130
Mm-hmm.
- How often?

10:16.130 --> 10:17.890
- Couple three times.

10:17.900 --> 10:20.400
He's the one
shot outside, right?

10:20.400 --> 10:22.570
- What can you tell me
about them?

10:22.570 --> 10:25.100
- He was Grey goose;
She was Miller lite.

10:25.100 --> 10:26.970
- The other night, did they
come in together?

10:26.970 --> 10:29.540
- No, she was at the bar alone.

10:29.540 --> 10:31.540
I remember because she ordered
the fried calamari

10:31.540 --> 10:33.010
and then didn't touch it.

10:33.010 --> 10:36.380
Then he turns up maybe
ten minutes later and digs in.

10:37.950 --> 10:39.080
- You didn't happen to hear

10:39.080 --> 10:40.880
what they were talking about,
did you?

10:40.890 --> 10:42.990
- When he sat down,
she says right away,

10:42.990 --> 10:45.060
"did you tell her yet?"

10:45.060 --> 10:46.460
Something like that.

10:50.660 --> 10:52.930
- Have you seen this girl?

10:59.140 --> 11:01.510
- I got her.

11:03.470 --> 11:05.110
- Caitlin, stop!

11:16.920 --> 11:17.920
Uhh!

11:22.690 --> 11:24.690
- Ow!
What the hell?!

11:31.040 --> 11:33.140
- Bitch bit me.

11:37.180 --> 11:40.040
- Lex Talionis, baby.

11:40.050 --> 11:42.450
- Yeah.
- Should've bit her back.

11:47.620 --> 11:51.820
<i>- Friday night, I got my tattoo
at the ink tank on Belmont.</i>

11:51.820 --> 11:53.220
<i>Is that a crime now?</i>

11:53.230 --> 11:56.460
- It is if you're under 18.
- Barbara signed for me.

11:56.460 --> 11:57.830
- We both know that's crap,
Caitlin.

11:57.830 --> 11:59.460
- Get away from me!

11:59.470 --> 12:00.730
- And you got
"an eye for an eye"

12:00.730 --> 12:02.770
because you're a fan of Gandhi?

12:02.770 --> 12:04.700
- Yeah, this is America.

12:04.700 --> 12:06.770
I live with a judge, remember?
I know my rights.

12:06.770 --> 12:08.170
- We asked if you
wanted a lawyer.

12:08.170 --> 12:10.810
You said no.
- Yeah, but I'm a minor.

12:10.810 --> 12:12.640
- And we have a subpoena.

12:12.640 --> 12:14.580
- If you're gonna go all
constitutional on us,

12:14.580 --> 12:18.250
for resisting arrest,
assaulting a police officer,

12:18.250 --> 12:19.780
and obstructing
an investigation.

12:19.790 --> 12:21.720
- Why don't you
just suck my ass?

12:21.720 --> 12:24.720
- Wow. No wonder
you haven't been adopted.

12:26.860 --> 12:28.530
- Okay.

12:29.860 --> 12:31.860
Mrs. Kinzie said you were
fighting with the judge.

12:31.860 --> 12:33.530
What about?

12:33.530 --> 12:36.530
- I said he was a douche.
He disagreed.

12:36.540 --> 12:37.900
- Maybe we can be more specific.

12:37.900 --> 12:40.570
- The dude monitored my phone
like I was 12.

12:40.570 --> 12:43.240
He inspected my outfit like he
was the frickin' fashion police.

12:43.240 --> 12:47.210
That's what a father...
- he's not my father!

12:49.880 --> 12:51.750
He didn't care about me.

12:51.750 --> 12:53.550
<i>I was just his rent-a-kid</i>

12:53.550 --> 12:57.220
to ease his rich suburban guilt.

12:57.890 --> 12:59.520
- Did he hurt you?

12:59.530 --> 13:01.830
Because if he did...
- huh? No. Gross.

13:02.590 --> 13:04.560
<i>Are we done here?</i>

13:04.560 --> 13:07.560
- Not even close.

13:07.570 --> 13:08.690
- Give me a minute with her.

13:15.210 --> 13:16.810
- Watch out.
She bites.

13:28.220 --> 13:29.920
<i>- I'm Asa Valdez.</i>

13:29.920 --> 13:31.320
- Yeah?

13:31.320 --> 13:33.290
Your mommy coming to pick you up
after work?

13:33.290 --> 13:34.320
- I know yours was doing life

13:34.330 --> 13:36.730
until she was Shanked
in the shower.

13:36.730 --> 13:38.330
- Yeah.

13:39.830 --> 13:42.570
Well, it's tough being
a crack whore.

13:43.800 --> 13:45.340
- The Kinzies took you in.

13:45.340 --> 13:47.000
They cleaned you up,
gave you a home.

13:47.010 --> 13:49.310
- Like I said, guilt makes
people do all k...

13:49.310 --> 13:51.880
- still, you took a bat
to the windows of his car.

13:51.880 --> 13:55.980
He could've had you arrested,
but he didn't.

13:55.980 --> 13:57.980
Why is that, Caitlin?

13:59.580 --> 14:01.280
- You're Anna Valdez.

14:04.360 --> 14:06.920
He said
I could be just like you.

14:09.760 --> 14:12.730
- I don't think you
killed him, Caitlin,

14:12.730 --> 14:14.360
but I got to tell you,
things are not looking good

14:14.370 --> 14:16.700
for you right now.
- Like I care.

14:16.700 --> 14:19.640
- You care a lot.
I know you do.

14:21.710 --> 14:24.310
Judge Kinzie showed me
the birthday card you gave him.

14:24.310 --> 14:27.940
You wrote, "thank you
for saving my life."

14:28.850 --> 14:33.050
The Kinzies were the best thing
that ever happened to you.

14:33.050 --> 14:34.720
If you were gonna kill him,

14:34.720 --> 14:37.390
why'd you break his
car windows first?

14:37.390 --> 14:38.760
That only points
all fingers at you.

14:38.760 --> 14:41.390
I know you're smarter than that.

14:41.390 --> 14:44.360
Ray told me about
your boyfriend's death.

14:44.360 --> 14:46.000
Tell me about Orlando.

14:47.830 --> 14:49.830
- Oh, my god.

14:53.700 --> 14:55.870
You were screwing him.

14:57.080 --> 14:59.380
- Can I speak with you?
- Did you kill him?

14:59.380 --> 15:01.010
- Now!

15:03.080 --> 15:05.050
Sit down!

15:06.280 --> 15:08.690
- Look who just got bit.
- Yeah.

15:12.360 --> 15:14.390
- I thought I could help.
- I don't want to hear it.

15:14.390 --> 15:15.760
I told you to stay away
from this case.

15:15.760 --> 15:19.030
- You're wasting your time.
- Go home.

15:20.030 --> 15:22.100
- Caitlin didn't kill Kinzie.

15:28.840 --> 15:31.010
- She did seem to know a lot
about the girl.

15:31.010 --> 15:34.040
- if they were,
a competent defense attorney

15:34.050 --> 15:36.150
will discredit anything
we learn from her.

15:36.150 --> 15:38.450
- And if they weren't?
- She's still a witness.

15:38.450 --> 15:41.380
If she's involved
as part of the prosecution team,

15:41.390 --> 15:44.920
her testimony will be tainted.
- Right.

15:44.920 --> 15:46.060
Looks like we have
to start digging

15:46.060 --> 15:48.960
through Caitlin's
foster care files.

15:48.960 --> 15:50.960
- Good luck.
- Heh.

15:57.800 --> 16:00.070
- Damn,
this girl had a rough life.

16:00.070 --> 16:01.400
Kinzie must've been a Saint.

16:01.410 --> 16:04.070
- Hmm, and father
Jack Calahan agrees.

16:04.080 --> 16:06.980
And I quote, "there are no
better foster candidates"

16:06.980 --> 16:10.410
than the Kinzies."
Everybody loves this guy.

16:10.420 --> 16:12.150
- Maybe that's his blessing
and his curse.

16:12.150 --> 16:14.020
Good-looking guy like Kinzie,

16:14.020 --> 16:18.150
hanging out in a bar
on a Friday night...

16:18.160 --> 16:20.820
If he were my husband,
I might be jealous.

16:20.830 --> 16:22.360
- And you'd hire somebody
to whack him?

16:22.360 --> 16:24.730
- It's easier than divorce.

16:24.730 --> 16:28.400
- Tell me about it.
Listen to this.

16:28.400 --> 16:31.970
"I heard Raymond Kinzie
wants to be a foster parent.

16:31.970 --> 16:33.840
"He's an awful judge
and an awful man

16:33.840 --> 16:36.110
"who hates women
and protects rapists.

16:36.110 --> 16:37.840
"Not only should he
be off the bench,

16:37.840 --> 16:39.110
"he should be off the planet.

16:39.110 --> 16:41.510
If you don't stop this, I will."

16:41.510 --> 16:45.980
- Signed?
- "A gravely concerned citizen."

16:45.980 --> 16:48.120
Now that's some anal-retentive
penmanship.

16:48.120 --> 16:50.190
I mean, who the hell even
writes a letter these days?

16:50.190 --> 16:53.490
- Someone whose rapist is being
protected by judge Kinzie?

17:00.870 --> 17:03.900
In his 15 years on the bench,

17:03.900 --> 17:06.839
Kinzie tried 47 rapes.

17:08.040 --> 17:10.140
- Maybe we can narrow it down
with this.

17:13.079 --> 17:15.550
- Nagel confirmed
Caitlin's alibi.

17:15.550 --> 17:16.980
- I figured as much.

17:23.819 --> 17:25.920
Why don't you just ask me?

17:26.890 --> 17:28.560
- Ask you what?

17:28.560 --> 17:31.560
